### Q: "Prisma?"
**YES, great call.** Prisma replaces raw Supabase JS queries. Here's why:

| Aspect | Without Prisma (Supabase JS) | With Prisma |
|--------|-----|------|
| Query style | `supabase.from('issues').select('*')` | `prisma.issue.findMany()` |
| Type safety | ❌ No types, runtime errors | ✅ Full TypeScript types auto-generated |
| Migrations | Manual SQL files | `prisma migrate dev` — automatic |
| Schema | Written in SQL | `schema.prisma` — readable DSL |
| Relations | Manual joins | Auto-resolved: `issue.department`, `issue.comments` |
| Learning value | Low | 🔥 Prisma is THE most in-demand ORM in Node.js |

### Q: "Can we change JS to another language?"
**Backend → TypeScript.** It's JavaScript but with superpowers:
```typescript
// JavaScript — no safety net
function getUser(id) {
  return db.query(id);  // What type is id? string? number? Who knows!
}

// TypeScript — compiler catches bugs BEFORE runtime
function getUser(id: string): Promise<User> {
  return prisma.user.findUnique({ where: { id } });  // Type-safe!
}
```
Frontend stays JS because migrating React components to TS would double the scope.

