### Every Framework & Library Explained

#### Backend Stack
| Package | What It Is | Why We Use It | What You'll Learn |
|---------|-----------|--------------|-------------------|
| **Express.js** | HTTP server framework | Industry standard, 60%+ of Node.js APIs use it | Routing, middleware pattern, request lifecycle |
| **TypeScript** | Typed superset of JavaScript | Catches bugs at compile-time, better IDE support | Static typing, interfaces, generics, type inference |
| **Prisma** | ORM (Object-Relational Mapper) | Type-safe DB queries, auto-migrations, schema DSL | Database modeling, relations, migrations, query optimization |
| **helmet** | Security middleware | Sets 15+ HTTP security headers automatically | Web security headers (CSP, HSTS, X-Frame, etc.) |
| **cors** | CORS middleware | Controls which domains can call our API | Cross-Origin Resource Sharing, browser security model |
| **express-rate-limit** | Rate limiter | Prevents DDoS, brute-force attacks | API abuse prevention, sliding window algorithms |
| **express-validator** | Input validation | Validates & sanitizes all user input | Input validation patterns, sanitization |
| **jsonwebtoken** | JWT library | Verify Supabase auth tokens server-side | JWT structure (header.payload.signature), token verification |
| **multer** | File upload handler | Handles multipart form data (image uploads) | File streams, memory storage, size limits |
| **@google/generative-ai** | Gemini SDK | AI image analysis + categorization | AI prompt engineering, multimodal AI, structured output |
| **morgan** | HTTP logger | Logs every API request | Request logging, debugging, monitoring |
| **dotenv** | Env loader | Loads `.env` variables | Environment management, secret handling |
| **@supabase/supabase-js** | Supabase client | Auth operations (signup, OTP, verify) | Managed auth, JWT flow, social providers |
| **tsx** | TypeScript executor | Run `.ts` files directly without compiling | Dev workflow, TypeScript execution |
| **zod** | Schema validation | Runtime type validation (complements TypeScript) | Schema-first validation, type inference |

