## Geolocation & Map Architecture

### How Location Works (New System)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as 📱 Citizen App
    participant GPS as 📍 Browser GPS API
    participant API as ⚡ Backend API
    participant DB as 🐘 PostGIS DB
    participant Map as 🗺️ Leaflet Map

    User->>GPS: navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition()
    GPS-->>User: { lat: 26.85, lon: 75.80 }

    Note over User: Home Screen loads
    User->>API: GET /api/issues/nearby?lat=26.85&lon=75.80&radius=5000
    API->>DB: SELECT * FROM issues WHERE<br/>ST_DWithin(geom, ST_Point(75.80, 26.85)::geography, 5000)
    DB-->>API: Issues within 5km
    API-->>User: JSON array of nearby issues
    User->>Map: Render markers with criticality colors

    Note over User: Reporting new issue
    User->>GPS: Get current location
    GPS-->>User: { lat: 26.852, lon: 75.803 }
    User->>API: POST /api/issues { lat, lon, image, ... }
    API->>DB: INSERT with ST_Point geometry
    API-->>User: Issue created with location marker
```

### PostGIS Spatial Queries
```sql
-- Enable PostGIS extension (one-time in Supabase)
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS postgis;

-- Add geometry column to issues
ALTER TABLE issues ADD COLUMN geom geometry(Point, 4326);

-- Create spatial index for fast queries
CREATE INDEX idx_issues_geom ON issues USING GIST(geom);

-- Trigger: auto-populate geom from lat/lon on insert
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION update_geom()
RETURNS TRIGGER AS $$
BEGIN
  NEW.geom = ST_SetSRID(ST_MakePoint(NEW.longitude, NEW.latitude), 4326);
  RETURN NEW;
END;
$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql;

CREATE TRIGGER trg_issues_geom
BEFORE INSERT OR UPDATE ON issues
FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION update_geom();

-- Query: Find all issues within 5km of user's location
SELECT *, ST_Distance(
  geom::geography,
  ST_SetSRID(ST_MakePoint($lon, $lat), 4326)::geography
) AS distance_meters
FROM issues
WHERE ST_DWithin(
  geom::geography,
  ST_SetSRID(ST_MakePoint($lon, $lat), 4326)::geography,
  5000  -- 5km radius in meters
)
ORDER BY distance_meters ASC;
```

