## Gemini AI — Smart Categorization + Criticality

### Prompt Engineering
```
You are a civic infrastructure analyst. Analyze this image of a civic issue.

TASK 1 — CATEGORIZE into exactly ONE department:
- Water Department (leaks, contamination, flooding, supply disruption)
- Roads & Infrastructure (potholes, cracks, sidewalks, bridges)
- Electricity (streetlights out, exposed wires, transformer issues)
- Sanitation & Waste (garbage overflow, illegal dump, blocked drains)
- Traffic & Transport (signal malfunction, parking, highway damage)
- Urban Development (construction hazard, building violation)
- Parks & Environment (tree fallen, park damage, pollution, stray animals)
- General Administration (other civic issues)

TASK 2 — ASSESS CRITICALITY:
- critical: Immediate danger to life/safety (exposed wires, structural collapse, flooding)
- high: Serious hazard needing urgent attention within 24h (large potholes, water main break)
- medium: Notable issue needing attention within a week (streetlight out, garbage)
- low: Minor inconvenience (cosmetic damage, faded paint)

TASK 3 — GENERATE DETAILS:
- title: Concise issue title (max 8 words)
- description: Detailed description (2-3 sentences)

Return ONLY valid JSON:
{
  "title": "...",
  "description": "...",
  "department": "Water Department",
  "criticality": "high"
}
```

